//! A node that checks if an Option value is Some (valid/not null).
//!
//! This node takes an Option value as input and returns true if the value is Some (i.e., valid or not null), and false if it is None.
//! Useful for validating optional data, handling present values, or controlling flow based on the presence of a value.
//!
//! # Inputs
//! - `in_value_option`: The Option value to check.
//!
//! # Outputs
//! - Returns `true` if the Option is Some, `false` otherwise.
//!
//! # Example
//! If `in_value_option` is Some(42), the output will be true. If it is None, the output will be false.
//!
//! # Notes
//! Use this node to detect valid or present data in optional fields.

/// Check if an Option value is Some (valid/not null).
fn @[pulsar_node_fn_id]@() -> bool {
    @[in_value_option]@.is_some()
}